.SH "H5I ENV CREATE"
Create an isolated environment: code branch + git worktree under .git/.h5i/env/, a forked reasoning branch, and a pinned, fail-closed policy. The base revision is frozen at creation
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBcreate\fR [\fB\-\-from\fR] [\fB\-\-pr\fR] [\fB\-\-remote\fR] [\fB\-\-profile\fR] [\fB\-\-isolation\fR] [\fB\-\-backend\fR] [\fB\-\-audit\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-from\fR \fI<FROM>\fR
Base revision (default: HEAD). Pinned immutably
.TP
\fB\-\-pr\fR \fI<NUMBER|URL>\fR
Base the env on a GitHub pull request (number, #number, or URL): fetches refs/pull/<n>/head from the remote, pins it as the immutable base, and points the env\*(Aqs parent branch at a local `pr/<n>` tracking branch \(em so propose/apply review the PR head, and apply prints the push\-back command. Needs only `git`; `gh` (optional) enriches the push\-back hint with the PR\*(Aqs head branch name
.TP
\fB\-\-remote\fR \fI<REMOTE>\fR [default: origin]
Remote to fetch the PR head from (with \-\-pr)
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR \fI<PROFILE>\fR
Policy profile from .h5i/env.toml. Built\-ins need no file: `agent` (agent\-in\-box, scoped to $H5I_AGENT\*(Aqs runtime), `agent\-claude` / `agent\-codex` (pin one runtime: only that agent\*(Aqs HOME state + API egress), and `default` (fail\-closed build/test confinement). Unset auto\-picks the creating runtime\*(Aqs agent profile when this host can enforce it, else `default`
.TP
\fB\-\-isolation\fR \fI<ISOLATION>\fR
Isolation: auto (default) | workspace | process | supervised | container | hardened\-container | microvm. `auto` (or unset) picks the strongest tier the host can run; an explicit tier fails closed if the host cannot satisfy it (never silently downgrades)
.TP
\fB\-\-backend\fR \fI<BACKEND>\fR [default: auto]
Workspace backend (auto|worktree)
.TP
\fB\-\-audit\fR \fI<AUDIT>\fR [default: signal]
Audit capture mode for wrapped in\-env commands: signal (default) | all. `all` records every wrapped command, including small successful output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Environment name (lowercase slug, e.g. `fix\-auth`)
.SH "H5I ENV RUN"
Run a command inside an environment, policy-enforced and capture-wrapped: exit code passes through, evidence lands in refs/h5i/objects tagged with the env id + policy digest
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBrun\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> [\fICOMMAND\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Environment name (slug, `agent/slug`, or full `env/agent/slug`)
.TP
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
The command to run, after `\-\-`
.SH "H5I ENV SHELL"
Open an interactive, confined session INSIDE the environment \(em the "agent-in-box". stdio is inherited (a real terminal), so every command the session spawns is contained by the box, not by the agent choosing to wrap each call. Defaults to a login shell when no command is given
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBshell\fR [\fB\-\-readonly\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> [\fICOMMAND\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-readonly\fR
Attach as a READ\-ONLY observer: `$WORK` is pinned read\-only, the box gets an ephemeral per\-session HOME/tmp, and no env state (status, captures, manifest) is touched. Multiple `\-\-readonly` sessions can run on one env at once (they take a shared lock); they still exclude a live read\-write session. Requires isolation=process or supervised
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Environment name (slug, `agent/slug`, or full `env/agent/slug`)
.TP
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
Command to run inside the box (after `\-\-`); default: an interactive shell
.SH "H5I ENV ALLOW"
Manage the persistent user-level egress allowlist: extra hosts merged into every container-tier env whose profile already sets net.egress (a deny-all profile is never widened). Stored host-side under ~/.config/h5i/, outside every box-granted path; takes effect at the next `env run`/`env shell`. With no rule, lists the current entries
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBallow\fR [\fB\-\-remove\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIRULE\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-remove\fR
Remove the rule instead of adding it
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIRULE\fR]
Host rule: exact `api.example.com`, wildcard `.example.com` / `*.example.com`, optionally with a `:port` suffix
.SH "H5I ENV PROBE"
