.SH "H5I TEAM RUN"
Drive a full hands-off team cycle over the orchestra eDSL: dispatch -> independent attempts -> freeze -> mutual review -> revise -> neutral verify -> verdict (-> gated apply). Replaces scripts/team-run.sh; unlike the script it is journal-backed \(em re-running it resumes the cycle instead of starting over
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBrun\fR [\fB\-\-task\fR] [\fB\-\-task\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-manifest\fR] [\fB\-\-rounds\fR] [\fB\-\-verify\-cmd\fR] [\fB\-\-isolation\fR] [\fB\-\-apply\fR] [\fB\-\-gate\fR] [\fB\-\-launch\-resident\fR] [\fB\-\-poll\fR] [\fB\-\-timeout\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fITEAM\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-task\fR \fI<TASK>\fR
Task text to dispatch
.TP
\fB\-\-task\-file\fR \fI<TASK_FILE>\fR
Read the task from a file
.TP
\fB\-\-manifest\fR \fI<MANIFEST>\fR
TOML manifest parameterizing the run (task/rounds/verify/gate + optional agent enrollment). Flags below override manifest values
.TP
\fB\-\-rounds\fR \fI<ROUNDS>\fR [default: 1]
Maximum review->revise cycles (early exit on full approval)
.TP
\fB\-\-verify\-cmd\fR \fI<VERIFY_CMD>\fR
Neutral verifier command, e.g. \-\-verify\-cmd "cargo test \-q"
.TP
\fB\-\-isolation\fR \fI<ISOLATION>\fR
Isolation tier for the verifier (workspace|process|container|...)
.TP
\fB\-\-apply\fR
Apply the winner after an auto\-applicable verdict
.TP
\fB\-\-gate\fR
Ask a durable gate question before applying (implies apply on approval; the reply may arrive after this process exits \(em re\-run to resume at the gate)
.TP
\fB\-\-launch\-resident\fR
Spawn resident agent sessions in tmux (default: attach to already\-running sessions, e.g. from team\-launch.sh)
.TP
\fB\-\-poll\fR \fI<POLL>\fR [default: 15]
Poll interval while waiting on turns, seconds
.TP
\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fI<TIMEOUT>\fR [default: 1800]
Per\-turn wait budget, seconds
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the outcome as JSON
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fITEAM\fR]
Team id (default: the current team)
.SH "H5I TEAM TRACE"
