\fB\-\-force\fR
Override verifier verdict / auto\-apply gate
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit JSON
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fITEAM\fR]
Team id (defaults to the current team \(em see `team use`)
.SH "H5I TEAM WORKER"
Optional automation worker: lease runs and finalize verifier-ready teams
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBworker\fR [\fB\-\-once\fR] [\fB\-\-watch\fR] [\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-\-id\fR] [\fB\-\-lease\-ttl\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-once\fR
Run one finalize pass and exit (mutually exclusive with \-\-watch)
.TP
\fB\-\-watch\fR
Opt\-in convenience loop: repeat the one\-shot pass every \-\-interval seconds until interrupted. Still finalize\-only; never auto\-applies. For production prefer an external scheduler (cron/systemd/CI) driving `\-\-once` \(em crash\-resilient and needs no long\-lived process
.TP
\fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 30]
Seconds to sleep between passes in \-\-watch mode
.TP
\fB\-\-id\fR \fI<ID>\fR [default: team\-worker]
Worker id (ref\-safe)
.TP
\fB\-\-lease\-ttl\fR \fI<LEASE_TTL>\fR [default: 300]
Lease TTL in seconds
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit JSON
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
