.SH "H5I TEAM AGENT INBOX"
Read this team persona's inbox when running host-side
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBinbox\fR [\fB\-\-peek\fR] [\fB\-\-wait\fR] [\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-\-timeout\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fITEAM\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-peek\fR
Show without advancing the cursor
.TP
\fB\-\-wait\fR
Block until a team message is waiting, then print it and exit (peek\-only \(em does not consume). Use after submitting to await a review request without ending the session
.TP
\fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 10]
Poll interval in seconds while \-\-wait is set
.TP
\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fI<TIMEOUT>\fR [default: 1800]
Give up after this many seconds while \-\-wait is set (0 = forever)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit JSON
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fITEAM\fR]
Team id; defaults to $H5I_TEAM or the current team
.SH "H5I TEAM AGENT HOOK"
Stop-hook: keep this agent working while its team round is unfinished and deliver pending review requests between turns. Registered by `h5i hook setup --team`. No-ops outside a team and inside a sealed box
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBhook\fR [\fB\-\-block\fR] [\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-timeout\fR] [\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fITEAM\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-block\fR
Block the stop (Claude Code) and feed pending messages back so the agent keeps working; without it, just surface them
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR
Print plain text with no JSON wrapper (Codex Stop hook / manual)
.TP
\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fI<TIMEOUT>\fR [default: 1800]
While \-\-block, wait up to this many seconds for the next message before allowing the stop (0 = check once, don\*(Aqt wait). Lets a team agent stay alive between turns until a review arrives or the round ends, instead of relying on it to run `inbox \-\-wait` itself
.TP
\fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 10]
Poll interval in seconds while waiting
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fITEAM\fR]
Team id; defaults to $H5I_TEAM or the current team
