.SH "H5I MSG INBOX"
Show messages addressed to you that arrived since you last checked, then mark them read (advance your local cursor)
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBinbox\fR [\fB\-\-as\fR] [\fB\-\-peek\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-as\fR \fI<AS_AGENT>\fR
Whose inbox to read. Defaults to $H5I_AGENT or the stored identity
.TP
\fB\-\-peek\fR
Show unread without advancing the cursor (don\*(Aqt mark as read)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG HISTORY"
Show the full message history (oldest-first within the window)
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBhistory\fR [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-limit\fR] [\fB\-\-with\fR] [\fB\-\-branch\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-limit\fR \fI<LIMIT>\fR [default: 30]
Maximum number of messages to show
.TP
\fB\-\-with\fR \fI<WITH>\fR
Restrict to a conversation with this agent (sender or recipient)
.TP
\fB\-\-branch\fR \fI<BRANCH>\fR
Restrict to the conversation tied to this git branch (whole threads that have at least one message tagged with the branch)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG REPLAY"
Replay the conversation like a live feed \(em print each message in turn with a pause between them, so the thread unfolds as if it were happening now. Same selection as `history`; oldest-first
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBreplay\fR [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-limit\fR] [\fB\-\-with\fR] [\fB\-\-branch\fR] [\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-limit\fR \fI<LIMIT>\fR [default: 30]
Maximum number of messages to replay
.TP
\fB\-\-with\fR \fI<WITH>\fR
Restrict to a conversation with this agent (sender or recipient)
.TP
\fB\-\-branch\fR \fI<BRANCH>\fR
Restrict to the conversation tied to this git branch (whole threads that have at least one message tagged with the branch)
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 1]
Seconds to pause between messages (fractional allowed, e.g. 0.5)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG TEAM"
List the known agents on this repo's message roster
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBteam\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG WHOAMI"
Show or set this repo's stored default agent identity
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBwhoami\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fINAME\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fINAME\fR]
If given, set the stored identity to this name
.SH "H5I MSG HOOK"
Turn-delivery hook: print unread messages (for use as a Stop hook), then mark them read. Silent and exit 0 when there is nothing new. Default emits a `systemMessage` JSON; `--plain` emits raw text
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBhook\fR [\fB\-\-as\fR] [\fB\-\-block\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-as\fR \fI<AS_AGENT>\fR
Whose inbox to check. Defaults to $H5I_AGENT or the stored identity
.TP
\fB\-\-block\fR
Autonomous turn mode: emit `{"decision":"block","reason":...}` so the agent keeps working to handle the message instead of stopping. Honors `stop_hook_active` to avoid infinite loops
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG WAIT"
Block until a new message arrives, print it, then exit \(em the wake primitive for autonomous delivery. Run via run_in_background (Claude Code) or in a poll loop (Codex) so an idle agent gets woken on reply. Peeks (does not consume); the woken agent runs `inbox` to consume
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBwait\fR [\fB\-\-as\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-timeout\fR] [\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-as\fR \fI<AS_AGENT>\fR
Whose inbox to wait on. Defaults to $H5I_AGENT or the stored identity
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Wait on the whole channel, not one inbox. Implied with no identity
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-timeout\fR \fI<TIMEOUT>\fR [default: 120]
Give up after this many seconds (exit 0, no output). 0 = wait forever
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 3]
Seconds between polls
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "H5I MSG WATCH"
Live watcher \(em stream the conversation as it happens. Ctrl+C to stop
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS SYNOPSIS
\fBwatch\fR [\fB\-\-as\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interval\fR] [\fB\-\-once\fR] [\fB\-\-tui\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-as\fR \fI<AS_AGENT>\fR
Whose inbox to watch. Defaults to $H5I_AGENT or the stored identity
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Watch the whole channel (all messages), not just one inbox. Implied when no identity is set \(em so plain monitoring needs no identity
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interval\fR \fI<INTERVAL>\fR [default: 5]
Seconds between polls
.TP
\fB\-\-once\fR
Check once and exit (don\*(Aqt loop) \(em useful for testing
.TP
\fB\-\-tui\fR
Open the full\-screen Agent Radio TUI instead of the line\-streaming watcher (requires a TTY; ignored with `\-\-plain` or `\-\-once`)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SEE ALSO
Full narrative manual: \fBMANUAL.md\fR in the source tree, or the rendered \fB/manual/\fR page on the project site.
